<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920318-0107</DOCNO><DOCID>920318-0107.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Amtech Corp.:   Stock Offering Is Planned   Totaling 2.2 Million Shares</HL><DATE>03/18/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B3</SO><CO>   AMTC APS J.MIB</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>INITIAL PUBLIC OFFERINGS (INI)HEAVY MACHINERY (MAC)MARINE TRANSPORTATION (MAR)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)SEMICONDUCTORS, INTEGRATED CHIPS (SEM)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)</IN><NS>INITIAL PUBLIC OFFERINGS (INI)BOND AND STOCK REGISTRATIONS AND PRICINGS (REG)STOCK MARKET NEWS (STK)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)FAR EAST (FE)JAPAN (JA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Amtech Corp. said it filed a registration statement withthe Securities and Exchange Commission for an offering of 2.2million shares, including 625,000 to be sold by shareholders.   The 1.3 million offered by the company will increase totalshares outstanding to about 11.3 million, said the Dallasprovider of electronic identification systems.</LP><TEXT>   Amtech said it plans to use the proceeds for workingcapital, research and development, increased marketing,capital expenditures to expand manufacturing capacity andother general purposes.   Amtech said that 400,000 shares would be sold by AmericanPresident Cos. and 225,000 would be sold by Mitsubishi Corp.,Amtech's Asian distributor. Amtech said that both companieswill retain substantial stakes in Amtech after the offering.   Alex. Brown andamp; Sons Inc. is leading the underwriting group.</TEXT></DOC>